The sign is wrong. A jingle.
A television campaign.

710
00:47:40,107 --> 00:47:43,270
"The Desert lnn has heart"

711
00:47:45,913 --> 00:47:46,902
That's enough.

712
00:47:47,381 --> 00:47:51,181
The casino is our main means of income.

713
00:47:51,518 --> 00:47:55,818
Not the coffee shop, not the show.
The casino pays all our bills.

714
00:47:55,889 --> 00:47:59,120
If we give everybody's money back,
we can't pay our bills.

715
00:47:59,793 --> 00:48:01,385
We can't change our policy.

716
00:48:01,461 --> 00:48:03,622
Play a word game with me, this will do it.

717
00:48:03,697 --> 00:48:06,029
-What is a hunting lodge for?
-To hunt.

718
00:48:06,433 --> 00:48:08,993
-What do you do at a rest home?
-You rest.

719
00:48:09,069 --> 00:48:13,506
We'll associate the Inn with something
lovely. You don't think of anything, huh?

720
00:48:13,674 --> 00:48:17,235
Gambling. That's why people come here.
To gamble.

721
00:48:17,311 --> 00:48:21,941
They want to hunt, they go to Wisconsin.
To rest, they go to New Orleans.

722
00:48:22,149 --> 00:48:27,587
They want to gamble, they come to Vegas.
That's why it's "Las Vegas gambling."

723
00:48:27,854 --> 00:48:31,346
You see signs around here with guys
with guns shooting ducks?

724
00:48:31,491 --> 00:48:35,723
It's a gambling place. They don't shoot
ducks, raccoons, beavers.

725
00:48:35,896 --> 00:48:38,694
They come to gamble.
That's what we do here.

726
00:48:38,799 --> 00:48:41,063
You're a nice guy, you make me laugh...

727
00:48:41,134 --> 00:48:44,228
...but our policy is:
we can't give your money back.

728
00:48:44,438 --> 00:48:46,770
Say goodbye to your wife. I got to go.

729
00:48:47,107 --> 00:48:49,041
What about Miracle on 34th Street?

730
00:48:49,543 --> 00:48:51,511
-It's the Christmas movie.
-Yes, it was.

731
00:48:51,578 --> 00:48:52,806
There was Gimbel's...

732
00:48:52,879 --> 00:48:56,576
...who feared if they gave something up
they would lose.

733
00:48:56,783 --> 00:49:01,083
They wound up benefiting. He was afraid
he'd lose business to Macy's, but he didn't.

734
00:49:01,188 --> 00:49:03,748
It's the same situation.
This costs you nothing.

735
00:49:03,824 --> 00:49:07,453
To give us back our money is nothing.
You would be the one to benefit.

736
00:49:07,594 --> 00:49:08,652
Wrong.

737
00:49:09,129 --> 00:49:12,963
In that movie,
Santa Claus took care of everything.

738
00:49:13,033 --> 00:49:17,470
There was Macy's, Gimbel's,
but Santa Claus fixed the whole thing.

739
00:49:17,904 --> 00:49:19,394
We don't have Santa Claus.

740
00:49:19,940 --> 00:49:21,032
Then we get him.

741
00:49:21,475 --> 00:49:22,100
Who?

742
00:49:22,175 --> 00:49:26,805
Santa Claus! We get him!
That's the ad campaign. I have the chills.

743
00:49:27,047 --> 00:49:30,210
Santa Claus is on the billboard
handing us our nest egg.

744
00:49:30,550 --> 00:49:35,112
We associate, for the first time ever,
Christmas and Las Vegas.

745
00:49:35,222 --> 00:49:38,214
Las Vegas, a Christmas place to be.

746
00:49:39,326 --> 00:49:40,816
We're finished talking.

747
00:50:02,115 --> 00:50:05,016
I can't take this any more.
Say something. Anything.

748
00:50:05,252 --> 00:50:09,518
Yell, scream, drive off the road.
Anything. Just stop being so quiet.

749
00:50:10,057 --> 00:50:11,217
I'm fine.

750
00:50:11,491 --> 00:50:15,825
I feel horrible. I can't apologize enough.

751
00:50:17,497 --> 00:50:22,161
You'll make yourself sick. I understand.
If I was you, I'd be furious.

752
00:50:22,269 --> 00:50:25,432
But you just can't hold it in.
You've got to let it out.

753
00:50:26,173 --> 00:50:27,572
I'm fine.

754
00:50:28,442 --> 00:50:31,775
Obviously, I can't keep apologizing
for what I did, so...

755
00:50:32,546 --> 00:50:37,210
...let's talk about what we'll do. Our dream
is the same. We just don't have money.

756
00:50:37,284 --> 00:50:41,618
We should stop saying we don't have
any money because we do have some.

757
00:50:42,656 --> 00:50:44,385
We have $802.

758
00:50:44,991 --> 00:50:46,219
That's something.

759
00:50:46,493 --> 00:50:48,984
Yes, that's something.

760
00:50:52,232 --> 00:50:55,565
I think we should make the rest of the day
as pleasant as possible.

761
00:50:55,702 --> 00:50:58,193
We're headed towards Hoover Dam...

762
00:50:58,405 --> 00:51:00,805
...so why don't we make that
our destination?

763
00:51:01,041 --> 00:51:03,874
We could take a walk, maybe have a picnic.

764
00:51:03,977 --> 00:51:06,468
Get some fresh air. Wouldn't that be nice?

765
00:51:07,380 --> 00:51:09,109
-Is that what you'd like?
-Yes.

766
00:51:10,517 --> 00:51:12,849
Fine. Hoover Dam.

767
00:52:15,182 --> 00:52:16,843
Nice dam, huh?

768
00:52:22,989 --> 00:52:24,752
You want to go first or should I?

769
00:52:27,894 --> 00:52:29,259
-Are you hungry?
-No.

770
00:52:29,663 --> 00:52:30,755
I'm starving.

771
00:52:30,831 --> 00:52:33,664
-You shouldn't eat right now.
-Why?

772
00:52:34,167 --> 00:52:38,831
With the little money we have left,
let's not waste it on knick-knacks here.

773
00:52:39,406 --> 00:52:43,137
If that's your attitude, why don't you
give me my half of the money...

774
00:52:43,210 --> 00:52:47,579
...and you do whatever you want
with your half. That's the fair thing.

775
00:52:47,814 --> 00:52:50,305
"The fair thing"?

776
00:52:50,884 --> 00:52:54,547
I can't believe it! That's it!
I have been too controlled!

777
00:52:54,754 --> 00:52:58,986
You took our nest egg and broke it
all over the Desert lnn!

778
00:52:59,459 --> 00:53:03,691
You filled up the casino with yolk.
"The fair thing"! I was sleeping!

779
00:53:04,264 --> 00:53:07,631
-Get it out. Fine.
-Don't treat me like I'm an insane patient!

780
00:53:07,701 --> 00:53:11,228
Let's go back inside. You can yell at me.
But don't yell out here, okay?

781
00:53:11,304 --> 00:53:13,534
Out here? Out where? We live here.

782
00:53:13,607 --> 00:53:17,941
Get used to the cement, honey!
This is our house! Forever!

783
00:53:18,678 --> 00:53:21,340
This is it! We found ourselves.

784
00:53:21,581 --> 00:53:25,415
We found ourselves
in the middle of nowhere, with nothing!

785
00:53:26,086 --> 00:53:27,348
Where are you going?

786
00:53:31,825 --> 00:53:33,156
Please come inside.

787
00:53:40,133 --> 00:53:40,997
What is it?

788
00:53:41,067 --> 00:53:42,227
Sit down.

789
00:53:43,136 --> 00:53:44,626
-What is it?
-Just sit down.

790
00:53:47,674 --> 00:53:52,077
I apologize from the bottom of my heart.
I'll make it up to you.

791
00:53:52,479 --> 00:53:54,538
I'll make you breakfast in bed for life.

792
00:53:54,614 --> 00:53:56,946
Stay away from the food. You'll lose it.

793
00:53:58,251 --> 00:54:01,687
I just want to know how this happened.
I can't understand it.

794
00:54:01,788 --> 00:54:04,416
I just held things in so long I just burst.

795
00:54:04,758 --> 00:54:06,453
What did you hold in?

796
00:54:06,593 --> 00:54:07,491
Everything.

797
00:54:07,627 --> 00:54:11,119
You weren't the only one
whose life wasn't satisfying.

798
00:54:11,298 --> 00:54:15,098
I sat in that office for seven years
without a window.

799
00:54:15,368 --> 00:54:17,495
Sometimes I felt like I was going crazy.

800
00:54:17,704 --> 00:54:21,140
Why didn't you wake me up and say,
"l think I'm having this problem...

801
00:54:21,308 --> 00:54:25,244
"...can I go down and lose everything?"
Then I could've helped and maybe said no.

802
00:54:25,879 --> 00:54:29,747
I'm sure the Desert lnn has an all-night
shrink service, along with the spa.

803
00:54:29,916 --> 00:54:33,044
Someone could've counseled us.
He would've said, "Look...

804
00:54:33,653 --> 00:54:38,056
"...she's got to let it go. Spend $10,000
and rent the Goodyear blimp...

805
00:54:38,124 --> 00:54:40,649
"...and have her fly around
and flash positive things.

806
00:54:40,727 --> 00:54:42,718
"Much cheaper, same result."

807
00:54:45,365 --> 00:54:47,629
Why didn't you wake me up?
We could've talked.

808
00:54:47,968 --> 00:54:49,959
I didn't understand it until now.

809
00:54:51,504 --> 00:54:56,134
I'm glad you understand everything.
Unfortunately, I'm still screwed up.

810
00:54:56,776 --> 00:54:58,971
And we don't have the money to fix me.

811
00:54:59,346 --> 00:55:03,146
You're fixed, and we have
a couple of hundred for me.

812
00:55:03,750 --> 00:55:07,083
$100,000 for you, $100 for me.
I was sicker than you to begin with.

813
00:55:10,490 --> 00:55:15,359
I guess it was my fault. Maybe I just didn't
explain the nest egg well enough.

814
00:55:15,462 --> 00:55:18,454
If you had understood
that it's a very sacred thing.

815
00:55:18,765 --> 00:55:22,701
If you'd understood the nest egg principle,
as we will now call it...

816
00:55:22,769 --> 00:55:25,465
...in the first of many lectures
you will have to get.

817
00:55:25,739 --> 00:55:30,233
If we are ever to acquire another nest egg,
we both have to understand it.

818
00:55:30,677 --> 00:55:34,408
The egg is a protector like a god,
and we sit under the nest egg...

819
00:55:35,048 --> 00:55:39,508
...and we are protected by it.
Without it, no protection.

820
00:55:40,186 --> 00:55:44,350
It pours rain, the rain drops on the egg
and falls off the side.

821
00:55:44,691 --> 00:55:46,716
Without the egg, wet. It's over.

822
00:55:47,293 --> 00:55:49,853
But you didn't understand it,
that's why we're here.

823
00:55:49,929 --> 00:55:51,362
I understood the nest egg.

824
00:55:51,431 --> 00:55:53,296
Do me a favor. Don't use the word.

825
00:55:53,366 --> 00:55:55,834
You may not use that word!
It's off-limits to you.

826
00:55:56,336 --> 00:55:59,100
Only those who understand "nest egg"
may use it.

827
00:55:59,172 --> 00:56:02,471
Don't use any part of it either!
Don't use "nest" or "egg."

828
00:56:02,742 --> 00:56:06,508
If you're in the forest, you could say,
"That bird lives in a round stick."

829
00:56:06,880 --> 00:56:10,372
And you have "things"
over easy with toast.

830
00:56:14,187 --> 00:56:15,882
You know what I'd like to do?

831
00:56:16,489 --> 00:56:19,287
I'd like to give you
a small punishment before lunch...

832
00:56:19,559 --> 00:56:22,824
...and have you write 1,000 times
on the pavement:

833
00:56:23,296 --> 00:56:26,629
"I lost the nest egg."
Come on, say it 500 times.

834
00:56:26,766 --> 00:56:28,996
"I lost the nest egg. I lost the nest egg."

835
00:56:29,069 --> 00:56:31,230
I'm starting it for you. Jump in anywhere!

836
00:56:31,304 --> 00:56:33,534
"I lost the nest egg. I lost the nest egg!"

837
00:56:33,606 --> 00:56:35,335
Shut up on nest egg!

838
00:56:37,544 --> 00:56:40,445
Let me tell you,
that's not how you drop out.

839
00:56:40,513 --> 00:56:43,448
If you're really going to drop out,
you do it with nothing.

840
00:56:45,085 --> 00:56:47,918
Where did you read that,
in The Las Vegas Guide?

841
00:56:47,987 --> 00:56:50,683
I didn't read it.
Friends told me. People who know.

842
00:56:50,757 --> 00:56:55,057
You don't know anybody who knows.
You don't know any drop-outs except us!

843
00:56:55,128 --> 00:56:58,325
In Easy Rider, the movie
on which you're basing your whole life...

844
00:56:58,398 --> 00:57:00,559
...they had nothing. They had no nest egg!

845
00:57:00,633 --> 00:57:03,500
Bullshit! They had a giant nest egg.
They had cocaine.

846
00:57:03,570 --> 00:57:05,731
-That's not true.
-It is true.

847
00:57:06,106 --> 00:57:08,165
Linda, they sold cocaine.

848
00:57:09,242 --> 00:57:11,437
Okay, wait a second. Wait.

849
00:57:12,178 --> 00:57:15,807
I'm not going to stand here
arguing about an old movie.

850
00:57:16,015 --> 00:57:19,849
I'll go back inside. If you figure out a plan
to make $800 last a lifetime...

851
00:57:19,953 --> 00:57:21,545
...knock on the door.

852
00:57:21,855 --> 00:57:22,844
Forget it!

853
00:57:23,089 --> 00:57:24,954
-Forget what?
-Forget everything!

854
00:57:25,024 --> 00:57:29,324
The one good thing that came out of this
is that we forgot to remarry.

855
00:57:29,395 --> 00:57:32,455
That's the one good thing,
and no one has mentioned that yet.

856
00:57:32,832 --> 00:57:34,299
What does that mean?

857
00:57:34,367 --> 00:57:38,133
It means if we'd remarried
it would've been harder to get a divorce.

858
00:57:38,204 --> 00:57:42,140
Now it's easy. I'll stay in Nevada
for six weeks and we're through.

859
00:57:42,342 --> 00:57:43,775
You don't mean that.

860
00:57:44,110 --> 00:57:46,340
You bet your life I do.
'Cause you know what?

861
00:57:46,412 --> 00:57:50,712
I know you'll never let me forget this.
For the rest of our lives, you'll blame me.

862
00:57:50,884 --> 00:57:53,216
So goodbye. It' over. I'm sorry.

863
00:57:53,586 --> 00:57:56,646
Don't hitchhike here in Nevada.
I don't blame you for anything.

864
00:57:56,756 --> 00:57:59,953
You said get angry, and I got angry.
So it's over. Now stop it.

865
00:58:00,059 --> 00:58:01,890
It's not over. You're still yelling.

866
00:58:01,961 --> 00:58:05,863
I'm only yelling because you have
your hand out! Stop it!

867
00:58:05,932 --> 00:58:10,528
I have my dreams and I'll find somebody
who understands them and start over.

868
00:58:10,603 --> 00:58:14,095
I understand your dreams.
Will you take your arm back in?

869
00:58:14,674 --> 00:58:16,904
-Linda, don't do this.
-Get in.

870
00:58:17,277 --> 00:58:19,177
-Linda?
-Goodbye!

871
00:58:19,245 --> 00:58:23,579
Don't get in that car, goddamn it!
Don't get in that car! Stop!

872
00:58:53,146 --> 00:58:54,636
I've lost a woman.

873
00:58:55,181 --> 00:58:56,546
A whole woman.

874
00:59:41,461 --> 00:59:42,689
Just sit anywhere.

875
00:59:52,739 --> 00:59:54,434
She doesn't want to talk to you.

876
00:59:54,507 --> 00:59:57,738
It's my wife. It's between her and me.
But thank you for the ride.

877
00:59:57,810 --> 00:59:59,744
I said, she doesn't want to talk to you.

878
00:59:59,812 --> 01:00:03,339
Thank him for the ride,
tell him it was a family squabble.

879
01:00:04,717 --> 01:00:06,878
You don't listen real good, do you?

880
01:00:09,555 --> 01:00:13,013
By the time I count to three,
I want you out of here.

881
01:00:13,126 --> 01:00:16,095
I don't want you to count.
We'll both go. Honey, let's go.

882
01:00:16,562 --> 01:00:17,995
One, two...

883
01:00:18,064 --> 01:00:19,361
-...three.
-Here we go.

884
01:00:19,432 --> 01:00:21,525
Come on. We've got some fighting to do.

885
01:00:21,601 --> 01:00:24,593
I don't want to fight. He's going to kill me.

886
01:00:26,372 --> 01:00:28,306
Understand that this was my wife.

887
01:00:37,450 --> 01:00:39,645
You remind me of everything I hate.

888
01:00:39,752 --> 01:00:42,983
I believe you. I understand.

889
01:00:44,390 --> 01:00:47,382
-Call the police!
-Somebody call the police!

890
01:00:49,462 --> 01:00:52,295
Call him off! I beg you! Help, police!

891
01:00:53,800 --> 01:00:55,961
-Call the police!
-Somebody call the police!

892
01:00:58,104 --> 01:01:01,870
Call the police, huh? If I wasn't wanted,
I'd stay here and kick your ass.

893
01:01:03,076 --> 01:01:05,169
When things cool down, I'll be back.

894
01:01:05,411 --> 01:01:09,177
You're dead. You're history.
You're dead, pal.

895
01:01:09,515 --> 01:01:11,176
I'm dead, pal.

896
01:01:34,774 --> 01:01:37,607
-This is all of it?
-Yeah. Are you okay?

897
01:01:37,710 --> 01:01:40,838
I'm all right.
Next time, get a ride with a small woman.

898
01:01:41,114 --> 01:01:43,344
Everything will be okay.

899
01:01:43,416 --> 01:01:45,850
Weren't you scared?
What were you talking about?

900
01:01:47,653 --> 01:01:49,780
He was telling me his whole life story.

901
01:01:49,856 --> 01:01:53,792
He was divorced, kicked out of the army,
couldn't keep a job....

902
01:01:53,860 --> 01:01:56,351
-He escaped from prison.
-What did he do?

903
01:01:56,863 --> 01:02:01,197
According to him, those two guys
were dead when he got there.

904
01:02:03,035 --> 01:02:04,696
Well, I showed him, huh?

905
01:02:11,277 --> 01:02:13,370
Pity the man who chases me.

906
01:02:18,551 --> 01:02:19,916
That's not funny.

907
01:02:21,354 --> 01:02:23,879
-You'll laugh soon.
-No, I won't laugh soon.

908
01:02:24,757 --> 01:02:28,454
An adult is not supposed to get
a bloody nose. That's for children.

909
01:02:30,830 --> 01:02:33,230
-Don't make fun of me.
-Okay. I'm sorry.

910
01:02:37,403 --> 01:02:40,065
It's beautiful here, don't you think?

911
01:02:44,277 --> 01:02:46,404
-Where do you want to go?
-I don't know.

912
01:02:47,814 --> 01:02:51,375
-Where are we?
-I don't know. We're in Arizona.

913
01:02:53,820 --> 01:02:55,287
Want to go to Canada?

914
01:02:55,354 --> 01:02:57,515
-Canada?
-Yeah! Let's live in Canada.

915
01:02:57,590 --> 01:02:59,057
-The country?
-Yeah!

916
01:02:59,158 --> 01:03:02,150
Do you know how much
it is to fill up a Winnebago?

917
01:03:03,095 --> 01:03:07,088
It's Arizona or New Mexico,
that's about all we can do right now.

918
01:03:08,534 --> 01:03:10,399
Preferably downhill from here.

919
01:03:11,971 --> 01:03:13,632
I like Arizona.

920
01:03:13,739 --> 01:03:17,175
We'll drive till we find someplace we like.

921
01:03:18,311 --> 01:03:20,836
I think this whole thing
is a blessing in disguise.

922
01:03:20,947 --> 01:03:22,778
Don't start that. It's not.

923
01:03:22,849 --> 01:03:25,443
-Well, I do.
-It's not a blessing in disguise.

924
01:03:25,518 --> 01:03:27,679
I don't know what it is, but it's not that.

925
01:03:27,753 --> 01:03:28,981
Fine. You'll see.

926
01:03:33,793 --> 01:03:35,624
Oh, Linda!

927
01:03:35,695 --> 01:03:37,788
-What's wrong?
-Look.

928
01:03:38,364 --> 01:03:40,594
We're in hell. We entered hell. When?

929
01:03:40,933 --> 01:03:42,366
Maybe he doesn't mean us.

930
01:03:42,468 --> 01:03:44,868
He'll pull me over
to tell me who it really is.

931
01:03:47,073 --> 01:03:49,337
Us?

932
01:03:50,643 --> 01:03:51,473
It's us.

933
01:03:51,811 --> 01:03:53,802
I'm stopping.

934
01:03:54,680 --> 01:03:56,910
I'm driving a whale here.

935
01:04:10,663 --> 01:04:13,655
-What's he look like?
-Bad.

936
01:04:17,537 --> 01:04:20,529
I hate the walkup the worst. I hate it.

937
01:04:21,607 --> 01:04:23,541
Can I see your license and registration?

938
01:04:23,609 --> 01:04:25,634
-What was I doing?
-83 miles per hour.

939
01:04:25,711 --> 01:04:28,373
83? My speedometer--

940
01:04:28,481 --> 01:04:31,314
Could I see your license and registration?

941
01:04:36,322 --> 01:04:40,486
I just bought this and I know
that driving it out of LA--

942
01:04:40,560 --> 01:04:42,721
Just your license, please. Thank you.

943
01:04:44,530 --> 01:04:47,522
-Can I ask a question?
-Wait in the home, please.

944
01:04:51,971 --> 01:04:53,700
Wait in the home, please.

945
01:04:57,944 --> 01:05:00,276
Can I ask you a question, please?

946
01:05:02,114 --> 01:05:04,378
Maybe I was going 70 or 75...

947
01:05:04,450 --> 01:05:07,248
...but I don't think it's possible
I could go 83.

948
01:05:07,587 --> 01:05:09,521
-We have good radar.
-Radar?

949
01:05:10,122 --> 01:05:14,616
You can't use radar on this.
There's a metal ladder here.

950
01:05:14,727 --> 01:05:18,390
It's like an antenna.
We get cable, we don't even want it.

951
01:05:19,966 --> 01:05:23,231
We have a microwave oven.
Wouldn't that do something?

952
01:05:23,903 --> 01:05:25,894
Wouldn't that screw it up?

953
01:05:26,505 --> 01:05:28,769
The dealer told me this would happen.

954
01:05:29,075 --> 01:05:31,236
He said I'd get a ticket for no reason.

955
01:05:31,944 --> 01:05:33,104
Hey, buddy.

956
01:05:36,515 --> 01:05:38,312
Can I ask how much this will cost?

957
01:05:39,051 --> 01:05:41,212
$140 or $150.

958
01:05:41,454 --> 01:05:45,254
We can't pay that. That is too high.
It's too much money. We don't have it.

959
01:05:45,758 --> 01:05:47,419
This isn't a swap meet.

960
01:05:49,929 --> 01:05:51,658
Did you see Easy Rider?

961
01:05:51,964 --> 01:05:53,124
It doesn't work.

962
01:05:54,734 --> 01:05:56,725
You know, the movie Easy Rider?

963
01:05:57,603 --> 01:05:59,628
I can't believe you asked me that.

964
01:05:59,705 --> 01:06:03,835
That's my favorite movie.
I started riding motorcycles because of it.

965
01:06:03,909 --> 01:06:05,206
Why'd you ask me that?

966
01:06:05,277 --> 01:06:08,678
My husband has based his whole life
on that movie.

967
01:06:08,848 --> 01:06:11,282
Not my whole life.
Just the last couple of weeks.

968
01:06:15,021 --> 01:06:17,285
Remember the ending,
when they got blown away?

969
01:06:17,356 --> 01:06:18,323
Great ending.

970
01:06:18,391 --> 01:06:20,086
It made my day.

971
01:06:23,195 --> 01:06:25,686
Remember Jack Nicholson
with the football helmet?

972
01:06:26,132 --> 01:06:28,692
Yes. Nicholson wasn't supposed
to get that part.

973
01:06:28,768 --> 01:06:31,498
-Really?
-No. He lucked into it.

974
01:06:31,671 --> 01:06:34,196
-Remember the scene in the commune?
-With the mimes?

975
01:06:34,306 --> 01:06:35,898
-Yeah.
-Great scene.

976
01:06:35,975 --> 01:06:39,570
Since we all have this in common,
couldn't you maybe let us go this time?

977
01:06:39,645 --> 01:06:43,604
That would be great.
This is like a club, isn't it?

978
01:06:44,517 --> 01:06:45,882
Get out of here.

979
01:06:46,118 --> 01:06:48,552
Dennis Hopper wouldn't give
Peter Fonda a ticket.

980
01:06:48,621 --> 01:06:50,714
Dennis Hopper couldn't find Peter Fonda.

981
01:06:51,357 --> 01:06:54,849
You were real nice. I appreciate it.
That's terrific.

982
01:06:55,194 --> 01:06:56,718
Did you see The Terminator?

983
01:06:56,796 --> 01:06:58,764
No, I didn't. Heard about it, though.

984
01:06:58,831 --> 01:07:00,799
You should see it. You look like him.

985
01:07:00,966 --> 01:07:01,933
Thank you.

986
01:07:14,280 --> 01:07:16,111
You're up $140.

987
01:07:47,580 --> 01:07:49,241
Where are we now?

988
01:07:49,648 --> 01:07:51,081
What does that sign say?

989
01:07:51,617 --> 01:07:53,949
Safford, Arizona.

990
01:07:54,153 --> 01:07:56,815
My legs are asleep. Let's live here.

991
01:08:25,651 --> 01:08:29,985
Kind of nice having young people here.
I like it.

992
01:08:43,102 --> 01:08:45,935
Four more, three more....

993
01:08:50,709 --> 01:08:53,200
Head looks right and left and bend.

994
01:08:57,016 --> 01:09:01,350
Honey! Come on. Breakfast is ready.

995
01:09:03,122 --> 01:09:05,147
-You look nice.
-Good morning.

996
01:09:12,331 --> 01:09:14,162
Last night was amazing.

997
01:09:18,337 --> 01:09:21,329
-Where did we get this?
-We brought it with us.

998
01:09:24,743 --> 01:09:26,734
Here's your coffee. Some eggs?

999
01:09:27,346 --> 01:09:28,506
Cereal?

1000
01:09:29,548 --> 01:09:31,709
Let's save the rest of the food.

1001
01:09:34,153 --> 01:09:35,745
What time did you get up?

1002
01:09:35,821 --> 01:09:38,984
I've been up for hours.
I've been all over this place.

1003
01:09:39,525 --> 01:09:42,858
At the end of the road,
there's this sweet little creek.

1004
01:09:42,995 --> 01:09:45,657
The people, three doors down,
have this little garden--

1005
01:09:45,731 --> 01:09:48,291
Doctor says I'm losing the sight
in my right eye.

1006
01:09:48,667 --> 01:09:49,861
I can't hear you.

1007
01:09:50,002 --> 01:09:53,096
-I said, I'm losing my sight in my right eye!
-I can't hear you!

1008
01:09:54,206 --> 01:09:56,902
-I was thinking we could get a puppy.
-Puppy?

1009
01:09:57,977 --> 01:09:59,911
We have to get jobs today.

1010
01:10:00,279 --> 01:10:04,181
We'll get jobs today.
It'll be great. This is the beginning.

1011
01:10:04,250 --> 01:10:05,979
But for real. We need money.

1012
01:10:06,051 --> 01:10:07,746
We will. Great jobs. Today.

1013
01:10:08,921 --> 01:10:10,548
We have no plan of attack.

1014
01:10:10,623 --> 01:10:12,420
-I'm ready to go.
-What about me?

1015
01:10:12,491 --> 01:10:15,483
-Maybe we should go together?
-No, we should go separately.

1016
01:10:15,594 --> 01:10:17,585
That way we can cover more territory.

1017
01:10:17,963 --> 01:10:20,955
Be very careful. And get a very good job.

1018
01:10:21,300 --> 01:10:22,460
Today.

1019
01:10:22,768 --> 01:10:24,929
I challenge you. I bet I get one first.

1020
01:10:26,205 --> 01:10:28,036
Loser sleeps under the home.

1021
01:10:29,275 --> 01:10:31,869
-Try to be back before dark.
-I will.

1022
01:10:32,144 --> 01:10:33,475
Good luck.

1023
01:10:33,979 --> 01:10:35,344
Buy a cheap lunch.

1024
01:10:35,648 --> 01:10:37,172
Okay, bye-bye!

1025
01:11:58,797 --> 01:12:00,287
Excuse me.

1026
01:12:01,800 --> 01:12:03,961
You scared me. Good morning.

1027
01:12:04,336 --> 01:12:06,429
I'm interested in the delivery job.

1028
01:12:06,505 --> 01:12:08,666
-For your son?
-For myself.

1029
01:12:09,074 --> 01:12:10,234
For you?

1030
01:12:11,877 --> 01:12:13,811
-You have your own car?
-No.

1031
01:12:14,313 --> 01:12:16,838
It's a delivery job. You would need a car.

1032
01:12:17,116 --> 01:12:18,606
I have a motor home.

1033
01:12:18,684 --> 01:12:20,151
A motor home?

1034
01:12:21,587 --> 01:12:23,748
You couldn't buy gas
with what I'd pay you.

1035
01:12:24,390 --> 01:12:26,654
I thought maybe you'd provide the truck.

1036
01:12:26,725 --> 01:12:31,458
No, we don't do that. I was going
to get a high-school kid with a Rabbit.

1037
01:12:32,297 --> 01:12:35,789
I don't believe an older man
with a motor home would work out.

1038
01:12:36,335 --> 01:12:37,802
Well, thank you very much.

1039
01:12:38,070 --> 01:12:42,336
You know, I should change that sign...

1040
01:12:42,441 --> 01:12:45,342
...from "man" to "boy."
Delivery boy is more correct.

1041
01:12:45,778 --> 01:12:47,871
Leave the sign alone. It's fine.

1042
01:12:48,580 --> 01:12:50,775
Any high-paying jobs
in the immediate area?

1043
01:12:51,417 --> 01:12:52,611
Let me think.

1044
01:12:54,686 --> 01:12:56,677
Not in the immediate area.

1045
01:12:56,855 --> 01:12:58,618
In the outlying area?

1046
01:12:59,291 --> 01:13:02,556
I don't know of any high-paying jobs
in the whole country. Do you?

1047
01:13:03,062 --> 01:13:06,361
I used to, not now, though.

1048
01:13:06,698 --> 01:13:08,165
A little down on your luck?

1049
01:13:08,233 --> 01:13:10,201
-You don't want to hear.
-I sure would.

1050
01:13:12,104 --> 01:13:17,098
There's the employment office
down the street, about a half mile.

1051
01:13:17,743 --> 01:13:21,235
It's a small building, but you can't miss it.
Maybe they can help you.

1052
01:13:21,313 --> 01:13:22,803
All right. Thanks.

1053
01:13:36,795 --> 01:13:38,786
So, what can we do for you?

1054
01:13:38,897 --> 01:13:40,057
I need work.

1055
01:13:40,799 --> 01:13:43,495
What has been
your previous work experience?

1056
01:13:43,569 --> 01:13:46,333
For the last eight years,
I was with Ross & McMahon.

1057
01:13:46,405 --> 01:13:50,774
The last four of those as creative director.
You know them?

1058
01:13:51,110 --> 01:13:53,101
-No
-Advertising agency.

1059
01:13:53,178 --> 01:13:55,146
One of the biggest in the world.

1060
01:13:56,615 --> 01:13:59,379
Before that I worked
in and out of advertising...

1061
01:13:59,651 --> 01:14:02,211
...nothing to speak of, for about five years.

1062
01:14:03,956 --> 01:14:06,049
I worked in a catering truck for...

1063
01:14:06,125 --> 01:14:10,221
...seven months in Pittsburgh,
and made food.

1064
01:14:12,097 --> 01:14:16,090
I worked at a crisis center
for three months.

1065
01:14:18,003 --> 01:14:22,565
Not dealing directly with crises,
more just answering the phone.

1066
01:14:22,741 --> 01:14:25,869
The regular phone, not the crisis phone.

1067
01:14:26,645 --> 01:14:29,512
In high school,
I worked at a stuffed-fruit place.

1068
01:14:29,615 --> 01:14:32,311
We don't have to go back that far.
More recent.

1069
01:14:32,784 --> 01:14:35,412
Advertising. Eight years,
Ross & McMahon.

1070
01:14:35,521 --> 01:14:37,512
What was your previous salary?

1071
01:14:38,190 --> 01:14:42,684
$80,000 was the base salary,
and then I was on a bonus situation...

1072
01:14:42,761 --> 01:14:46,595
...which would give me
between $15,000 and $25,000...

1073
01:14:46,698 --> 01:14:50,190
...depending on the year we had.

1074
01:14:50,602 --> 01:14:52,763
Generally, $100,000.

1075
01:14:53,572 --> 01:14:55,164
$100,000?

1076
01:14:56,175 --> 01:14:58,200
Over what period of time
are we talking about?

1077
01:14:58,277 --> 01:15:00,404
-A year.
-A year?

1078
01:15:04,883 --> 01:15:06,350
-What's so funny?
-Nothing.

1079
01:15:06,652 --> 01:15:11,749
What brings you here?
Trying to double up on that income?

1080
01:15:15,861 --> 01:15:18,830
I've come here to live.
I'm trying to change my life.

1081
01:15:19,331 --> 01:15:22,357
You couldn't change your life on $100,000?

1082
01:15:24,736 --> 01:15:26,897
Have you got any jobs for me?

1083
01:15:27,306 --> 01:15:31,640
I don't have anything right now
that you'd be interested in.

1084
01:15:31,777 --> 01:15:33,540
Check back with me in a month.

1085
01:15:33,645 --> 01:15:36,409
I'm very interested. What do you have?

1086
01:15:36,815 --> 01:15:40,979
Coming from your position and salary,
you wouldn't be interested in it.

1087
01:15:41,053 --> 01:15:43,920
You don't know me.
I might love it. What is it?

1088
01:15:43,989 --> 01:15:45,820
A crossing guard.

1089
01:15:46,825 --> 01:15:49,157
-What is that?
-A crossing guard.

1090
01:15:49,328 --> 01:15:51,922
-At a school?
-Where else have you seen them work?

1091
01:15:52,097 --> 01:15:54,895
I didn't know if there were different kinds.

1092
01:15:56,735 --> 01:15:58,225
What does that pay?

1093
01:15:58,403 --> 01:15:59,870
$100,000.

1094
01:16:05,978 --> 01:16:07,411
What does it really pay?

1095
01:16:07,813 --> 01:16:10,509
It pays $5.50 an hour, plus benefits.

1096
01:16:10,682 --> 01:16:12,149
The benefits meaning?

1097
01:16:13,018 --> 01:16:15,452
You get a ride to and from school
if you need it.

1098
01:16:16,622 --> 01:16:21,616
Do you have anything at all?
Something in the executive file?

1099
01:16:21,693 --> 01:16:26,357
Or maybe you have
a white-collar box or something?

1100
01:16:26,698 --> 01:16:28,393
What sort of box would that be?

1101
01:16:28,834 --> 01:16:31,496
Just a box of higher paying jobs.

1102
01:16:32,671 --> 01:16:36,334
I know! You mean the $100,000 box!

1103
01:16:40,879 --> 01:16:44,474
I'm glad I could be your entertainment.
But I want to tell you something.

1104
01:16:44,549 --> 01:16:47,382
I made a statement.

1105
01:16:47,953 --> 01:16:50,012
-A statement?
-Yes.

1106
01:16:50,822 --> 01:16:52,653
Did you see Easy Rider?

1107
01:16:52,991 --> 01:16:56,051
No. I saw Easy Money.

1108
01:16:56,128 --> 01:17:00,064
Rodney Dangerfield, I like him.
That "no respect" bit is funny.

1109
01:17:14,546 --> 01:17:15,535
Hi, honey.

1110
01:17:25,791 --> 01:17:27,622
-Guess what.
-A job?

1111
01:17:27,859 --> 01:17:30,419
-I won't know for sure until tomorrow.
-Doing what?

1112
01:17:30,562 --> 01:17:32,359
I don't want to say anything but--

1113
01:17:32,431 --> 01:17:35,423
-Give me a hint.
-Assistant manager.

1114
01:17:36,134 --> 01:17:38,625
The manager's going to sleep on it tonight.

1115
01:17:38,704 --> 01:17:41,969
I won't say more. I'm superstitious.
I don't want to jinx it.

1116
01:17:42,174 --> 01:17:44,665
-I can't believe it.
-What about you?

1117
01:17:44,776 --> 01:17:46,107
I had some good leads.

1118
01:17:46,178 --> 01:17:47,577
Give me a hint.

1119
01:17:47,779 --> 01:17:49,872
I don't want to jinx mine either.

1120
01:17:50,048 --> 01:17:51,709
I understand.

1121
01:18:44,903 --> 01:18:47,565
Are you paid to sit on your ass? Let's go.

1122
01:18:47,906 --> 01:18:50,238
Get us across the street, retardo!

1123
01:18:50,509 --> 01:18:51,908
Don't call me "retardo."

1124
01:18:51,977 --> 01:18:53,535
Come on, retardo!

1125
01:18:53,678 --> 01:18:58,308
Right now, sucker. Let's go, now!
Across the street, now!

1126
01:18:58,450 --> 01:19:01,112
We ain't got time to wait.
We're already late.

1127
01:19:04,623 --> 01:19:07,456
You're goint to get hurt.
Just cross the street.

1128
01:19:08,960 --> 01:19:11,520
Get off your bike and walk it
across the street.

1129
01:19:11,596 --> 01:19:14,588
Walk your bike! I'm warning you!
Walk your bike!

1130
01:19:15,233 --> 01:19:16,700
Do you come from the dump?

1131
01:19:17,636 --> 01:19:19,900
I take no responsibility for your safety.

1132
01:19:19,971 --> 01:19:22,633
Just die for us and save us the problem.

1133
01:19:22,841 --> 01:19:24,832
Brillo pad, fathead!

1134
01:19:28,547 --> 01:19:31,710
I was a kid once. Get out of here, you--

1135
01:19:34,386 --> 01:19:37,219
Come on, fast! Fast!

1136
01:19:37,522 --> 01:19:40,514
Here we go, hey! Kill the child!

1137
01:20:27,973 --> 01:20:30,134
Hey, mister? Where am l?

1138
01:20:30,542 --> 01:20:31,873
Safford, Arizona.

1139
01:20:32,110 --> 01:20:34,271
Oh, my God! How do I get to LA?

1140
01:20:34,813 --> 01:20:36,974
-Do you know where 70 is?
-No.

1141
01:20:38,917 --> 01:20:42,250
Go about three and a half blocks.
You see that "Stop" sign?

1142
01:20:42,687 --> 01:20:45,656
Turn left, go all the way down
until you hit 70.

1143
01:20:45,757 --> 01:20:48,920
Get on 70. That turns into 60
and it takes you to Phoenix.

1144
01:20:49,461 --> 01:20:52,453
Let me understand that.
The "Stop" sign, turn left to 60--

1145
01:20:52,531 --> 01:20:55,193
What are you smelling?

1146
01:20:55,600 --> 01:20:57,329
Is this interior leather?

1147
01:20:57,502 --> 01:20:59,663
Yeah, it comes with the car.

1148
01:21:00,138 --> 01:21:02,629
-It's nice.
-It's lovely.

1149
01:21:03,642 --> 01:21:06,406
I go down to the "Stop" sign, turn left...

1150
01:21:06,511 --> 01:21:11,073
...go to 70. 70 takes me to 60,
then to Phoenix. Is that correct?

1151
01:21:11,716 --> 01:21:14,549
-Do you like this car?
-What's not to like?

1152
01:21:52,190 --> 01:21:53,521
What are you?

1153
01:21:53,592 --> 01:21:55,526
A crossing guard. What are you?

1154
01:21:55,627 --> 01:21:58,721
I'm the assistant manager
at the Der Wienerschnitzel.

1155
01:21:59,664 --> 01:22:00,631
The what?

1156
01:22:00,699 --> 01:22:04,760
The Der Wienerschnitzel.
The manager wanted to sleep on it.

1157
01:22:04,836 --> 01:22:08,272
He said right after I left, I got it.
He didn't know how to contact me.

1158
01:22:08,340 --> 01:22:10,501
That's the job you were waiting for?

1159
01:22:10,709 --> 01:22:12,734
-You sell hot dogs?
-Yeah.

1160
01:22:14,679 --> 01:22:16,340
This place is great!

1161
01:22:16,982 --> 01:22:19,212
When you flush the toilet,
where does it go?

1162
01:22:19,451 --> 01:22:20,349
Who is this?

1163
01:22:20,418 --> 01:22:22,249
This is Skip, the manager.

1164
01:22:22,621 --> 01:22:24,521
This is David, my husband.

1165
01:22:25,724 --> 01:22:27,021
You're the manager?

1166
01:22:27,325 --> 01:22:28,656
You slept on it?

1167
01:22:29,628 --> 01:22:30,720
He slept on it?

1168
01:22:33,198 --> 01:22:34,187
How you doing?

1169
01:22:34,499 --> 01:22:35,659
Call me Skippy.

1170
01:22:37,936 --> 01:22:39,528
Linda told me what you did.

1171
01:22:39,771 --> 01:22:41,295
The drop-out thing.

1172
01:22:41,706 --> 01:22:43,367
I really admire you.

1173
01:22:43,508 --> 01:22:45,339
When I'm old, I might do it.

1174
01:22:46,678 --> 01:22:48,373
Did she say what happened today?

1175
01:22:48,813 --> 01:22:50,940
He's tired. I'll tell him later.

1176
01:22:51,016 --> 01:22:52,916
No, I want to hear Skip talk.

1177
01:22:54,753 --> 01:22:55,913
Hello?

1178
01:22:56,054 --> 01:22:59,683
We have this frying machine.
We didn't really know how to use it...

1179
01:22:59,791 --> 01:23:03,784
...but the funny thing is we used it anyway.

1180
01:23:03,895 --> 01:23:07,888
We put the oil in, read the instructions,
threw the fries in....

1181
01:23:09,534 --> 01:23:12,901
They were done. Serve them.
She comes up to me and says:

1182
01:23:13,071 --> 01:23:15,232
"Skip, these fries are frozen."

1183
01:23:16,374 --> 01:23:20,674
So we look at them in the light
and we see they're frozen.

1184
01:23:20,745 --> 01:23:22,076
A little bit of ice.

1185
01:23:22,347 --> 01:23:23,871
You were eating them frozen?

1186
01:23:23,982 --> 01:23:25,711
What do you want me to do?

1187
01:23:26,651 --> 01:23:30,052
The point is, she saw this minor detail
on the first day.

1188
01:23:30,789 --> 01:23:34,384
Do you believe it? You've got a good wife.

1189
01:23:34,659 --> 01:23:36,126
That's why I married her.

1190
01:23:36,194 --> 01:23:37,593
That's why I hired her!

1191
01:23:39,698 --> 01:23:41,461
I want to talk to her.

1192
01:23:47,472 --> 01:23:48,734
Don't get me wrong.

1193
01:23:48,807 --> 01:23:52,675
I've had a lot of fun these last two weeks.

1194
01:23:53,411 --> 01:23:55,311
Things didn't go like we hoped...

1195
01:23:55,380 --> 01:23:59,214
...but if we're still together now,
after what happened, we won't split up.

1196
01:24:00,051 --> 01:24:03,214
That makes me feel great,
and I'm real happy.

1197
01:24:03,755 --> 01:24:06,588
Isn't that wonderful?
I told you this would be a blessing.

1198
01:24:07,058 --> 01:24:08,047
Right.

1199
01:24:09,394 --> 01:24:13,888
Given our age and these jobs,
we won't see another nest egg for....

1200
01:24:15,066 --> 01:24:18,058
Ever. We'll never see anything.

1201
01:24:25,443 --> 01:24:30,574
I think that there has to be
some better way to rebuild than this.

1202
01:24:31,449 --> 01:24:35,078
I thought of a plan
that might speed things up.

1203
01:24:35,453 --> 01:24:37,478
Maybe I should sound it out with you.

1204
01:24:37,889 --> 01:24:42,292
Really? I was kind of thinking
the same thing, too.

1205
01:24:42,427 --> 01:24:44,122
-You were?
-I was.

1206
01:24:44,195 --> 01:24:46,356
-What is it?
-What was your plan?

1207
01:24:46,431 --> 01:24:50,697
My plan is not a plan, just a back-up.
What's your plan?

1208
01:24:52,137 --> 01:24:55,231
I was thinking that we go to New York
as fast as we can.

1209
01:24:55,306 --> 01:24:56,933
-And I eat shit?
-Yeah.

1210
01:24:57,041 --> 01:24:58,406
My plan, too!

1211
01:25:01,112 --> 01:25:02,943
Skippy. Out.

1212
01:27:10,508 --> 01:27:11,236
Brad!

1213
01:27:14,712 --> 01:27:15,940
How are you?

1214
01:27:16,247 --> 01:27:18,545
Oh, my God! Stay away from me!

1215
01:27:24,789 --> 01:27:27,280
Brad, I was joking with you!

